    b"       Choose memory search hints for the selected task and current request.\x0a\x0a  "
    b"      The hints will drive memory search before the selected task runs.\x0a\x0a       "
    b" Stop once the hints look good enough for the request without thinking about it "
    b"too much.\x0a\x0a        Search surfaces:\x0a        - tags: exact memory tags. They are "
    b"not substring searched.\x0a        - strings.contains: case-insensitive text fragme"
    b"nts. Each value is checked\x0a          as a substring against searchable memory co"
    b"ntent.\x0a        - strings.equals: exact text values. Each value is checked for ex"
    b"act\x0a          equality against searchable memory content.\x0a\x0a        Optional outp"
    b"uts available in this step:\x0a        - candidate_memory: a vague remembered obser"
    b"vation that could be useful to\x0a          preserve.\x0a\x0a        Rules:\x0a        - Ret"
    b"urn only search hints and optional candidate_memory.\x0a        - Search hints are "
    b"alternatives during retrieval; a memory can be useful\x0a          when any positiv"
    b"e tag or string hint matches.\x0a        - Prefer tags.any_of for positive tag hint"
    b"s.\x0a        - Leave tags.all_of empty unless compatibility with older memories ne"
    b"eds it.\x0a        - Use tags.none_of only for clear exclusions.\x0a        - Use stri"
    b"ngs.contains for durable words or phrases that should appear\x0a          inside a "
    b"relevant memory.\x0a        - Use strings.equals only for exact text that should ma"
    b"tch a relevant\x0a          memory value as a whole.\x0a        - Prefer a small set o"
    b"f high-signal hints over broad keyword stuffing.\x0a        - Return empty arrays w"
