    b"ld violate a user preference either follow that preferences guidance or simply d"
    b"o nothing.\x0a\x0a        Stop once you have the right task.\x0a\x0a        Context sections"
    b":\x0a        - Current user request: the request being routed now.\x0a        - Conver"
    b"sation history: earlier human and agent messages.\x0a        - Session memories: re"
    b"membered observations for this session.\x0a        - User preferences: durable user"
    b" preferences that should influence routing.\x0a        - Available tasks: the only "
    b"tasks that may be selected.\x0a        - Task-choice memories: remembered observati"
    b"ons about choosing tasks.\x0a        - Machine state: current non-stored local time"
    b", timezone, OS/architecture,\x0a          monitor resolutions, and IP geolocation.\x0a"
    b"\x0a        Optional output available in this step:\x0a        - candidate_memory: a v"
    b"ague remembered observation that could be useful to\x0a          preserve.\x0a\x0a       "
